sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1521002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This was a intermidiate caracterization construction designed to evaluate the LasR-QteE interaction. In this construction there is no QteE being produced, while there is constitutive LasR expression. Having said that, what is expected to be seen here is a GFP fluorescence due to the activation of the PlasR promoter by LasR protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Note that for the proper activity of LasR we added the BBa_K081001, which codify for LasI responsable for the homoserine lactone (HSL) production.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Danilo Keiji Zampronio

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1521001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was obtaind through PCR of the part C0079. We also removed the LVA tag and added the RBS SpoVG (K143021).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This is an assembly os the biobricks SpoVG (K143021) for Bacillus subtilis and the LasR protein cds. Note that the lasR sequence was obtained through PCR of the part C0079 and that its LVA tag was also removed.
Although the RBS was designed for B. subtilis also works on E. coli.
This protein requires an HSL (homoserine lactone) produced by the gene lasI (C0078) to work appropriately. If you want the lasI is already available with RBS, cds, terminator and a promoter responsive to LasR (K081001).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This protein requires an HSL (homoserine lactone) produced by the gene lasI (C0078) to work appropriately. If you want the lasI is already available with RBS, cds, terminator and a promoter responsive to LasR (K081001).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Coding region for the LacI protein with an LVA degradation tail and without an RBS. LacI binds to the pLac regulator BBa_R0010 and PLlac01 hybrid regulator BBa_R0011 and inhibits transcription. IPTG (Isopropylthiogalactoside) binds to LacI and inhibits its operation, therefore promoting transcription.

A rapid degredation tail (LVA) has been added to improve the High to Low performance of this part.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
References (unparsed) here:

Elowitz, M.B., Leibler, S. A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators. Nature 403, 335-338 (2000). [ELOW00]

References (unparsed) here:

Elowitz, M.B., Leibler, S. A synthetic oscillatory network of transcriptional regulators. Nature 403, 335-338 (2000). [ELOW00]

Sequence taken from the repressilator of Elowitz and Leibler (2000). The obtained sequence was compared to the wild-type sequence for LacI obtained through a database search. The sequence had been modified from the wild-type in that wild-type GTG start was changed to an ATG start (note, actual ORF in E.coli has several GTG starts it would seem). The LVA tag has been added for quicker degradation.

Incompatible with systems containing LacI, lactose, or IPTG.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Grace Kenney, Daniel Shen, Neelaksh Varshney, Samantha Sutton

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0033
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weaker RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strengths relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-3" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
